recipeInstructions.text: Heat olive oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Add garlic and saut√© for 1-2 minutes or until just starting to colour.
Add tomato paste and stir until heated through, then gently fold in beans and parsley.
Add spinach leaves and stir to wilt. Turn off heat. Season to taste with pepper.
Place cheese slices on toast and top with bean mixture. Top with cherry tomatoes and parsley sprigs to serve.
